.TH "kdb_handle_escape" 9 "kdb_handle_escape" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kdb_handle_escape \- validity check on an accumulated escape sequence.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" kdb_handle_escape
.BI "(char *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t sz "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buf" 12
Accumulated escape characters to be examined. Note that buf
is not a string, it is an array of characters and need not be
nil terminated.
.IP "sz" 12
Number of accumulated escape characters.
.SH "RETURN"
-1 if the escape sequence is unwanted, 0 if it is incomplete,
otherwise it returns a mapped key value to pass to the upper layers.
